	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Instead of doing all the arguing and debating that goes on in these forums (since they don't help anyone coming here to get information), I'll just tell people how I set up my eight spell slots and people can take whatever they want from them. First of all, I'm a 54 cleric (and we be for some time it's looking like). My first spell slot is (and probably always will be) CH (Complete Healing). For any tank that you will group with at these levels (referring to 50+), CH is the most effiecent (sp?) healing spell, hands down. My second spell slot is Celestial Healing, which I use to heal DD meleers (usually below 2000 HPs like rogues, monks, and rangers) and priest classes (clerics, shaman, druids). Thrid is Reckoning (DD spell for 630). Whenever I am FoM and nobody is in need of a heal and fully buffed, I will nuke so that battles will be quicker and experience will flow faster. While some clerics will never nuke because they want to type-cast clerics as healer/buffer ONLY, that's fine with me because that's how they wish to play. I personally wish to strike down with divine judgement those that challenge the will of Brell Serilis, and that's the way I wish to play. The way I figure it, I can cast Reckoning and sit back down and med it back until I need to heal again. I do not nuke unless FoM, because we are primary healers. However, I do not see the point in healing a tank with 4000 HPs with Rememdy when I can nuke/med/nuke/med/CH heal for 3500HPs and be in the same mana position as someone that rem/med/rem/med/CH. The only difference is I have done 1260 damage, and they have not. The 4th spell slot is my level five stun spell. Whenever a MoBs mez breaks the first thing I do is stun the bastard! Why heal the enchanter after the MoB beats on him when I can stun, then chanter mezzes w/o being interrupted, and everyone is happy? Stun is also excellent in Seb when those pesky casters try to gate, or the Curates in KC that are trying to CH. I choose the level five one for two reasons. First of all, it's the fastest one and that is important when you need the MoB stopped, whether it's from attacking, casting, or running when snare breaks, FAST. Also, it doesn't do any damage, so if the chanter happens to mez before I stun the MoB I will not break the mez. My fifth spell slot is either second stun/undead DD/Divine Barrier and totally depends on the situation. If I'm in a regular group and not fighting any undead, then it's the second stun spell. If I'm going against undead, then it's the undead spell which is far more mana effective than the other cleric DD spells. If I'm doing AoE groups, then it's DB since I end up being the puller :). Sixth slot, is always Divine Aura which will give your tank time to get a MoB off you and/or give you chanter/necro time to mez something. Seventh slot is interchangeable and is where I switch out buffs (Heroic Bond, Symbol of Words, Symbol of Marzin) when in battle situations, with Heroic Bond being the one up most of the time. After a long and arduous fight where everyone is at good health, but down just a little bit (let's say 80h), why cast Remedy on everyone and blowing 175mana a pop when I can cast a group heal and refresh the HB buff at the same time? This is also the slot where I keep all-purpose spells for different occasions (fear when I'm traveling, root when solo'n some greenie to help a n00b get some lambent armor drop, and rez when I'm traveling to a zone like KC and get hit with 85 tells to PLEAZZZZZZZE do a rez upon zoning in). My eighth and final slot is the spell Remedy, which is a quick heal to be used on INT casters that need a heal NOW (ie Chanters). Why don't I put it up with the other heals? One reason is force of habit, since I've always had only my top two heals up until I got remedy (har har) and the other reason is so I can easily find and click it in case I don't feel like spamming the hell out of everyone's screen with my Remedy message over and over. Nothing would suck more than accedentially slipping and casting Celestial Healing on a dying chanter instead of remedy and there goes Mr./Mrs. Chanter Bye bye! So *whew* that's how I have my slots set up and it works great for me. If you do it some other way, please post and perhaps I will learn a little something from reading your opinion. However, I will learn nothing from anyone that posts &quot;You stupid! You not do like me you n00b!&quot; and neither will anyone else. Please remember that arguing on the internet is much like playing in the Special Olympics. Even if you win, you are still retarded.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
