			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok being a 56 cleric I'll explain my way of taking care of a group, first the buffs.<BR>
<BR>
1. Hero bond<BR>
2. Marzin<BR>
3. AoF via Donals gaunts.<BR>
<BR>
that is the order of the spells,<BR>
first, cast on yourself first. when your buffs start wearing off you know the others will be running off soon as well.<BR>
<BR>
Heroic Bond is a must, specially for a full group, good hp and ac and a decent duration. <BR>
<BR>
Marzin, expensive? maybe but 700 extra hps makes your job a HELLA lot easier when you have more time to med between heals.<BR>
<BR>
AoF. Ok this is one spell that you might want to upgrade with an actual spell rather than off of the Donals Gaunts, however, it also saves you mana.<BR>
<BR>
Heals, CH a must if you have any tank class in the group. <BR>
Divine Light? I wish I understood why I also fizzle to hell and back with this spell. when it works its great for caster class.<BR>
<BR>
Remedy, a great heal for casters getting smacked around a little.<BR>
<BR>
all other spells are useless as the mana usage for them is not worth casting.<BR>
<BR>
Mind you these are just my opinions on this but I've noticed that it does make my job as a cleric easier. More hps...more time to med.<BR>
<BR>

